The sample code should be like below:

To send an Ajax post request, you could use this : This will be taken care by Akshay
$.ajax({
     type: "POST",
     url: "updateGlobalFeatures",
     data: { name: " Benefits Tracker", enabled: true, resourceId:"11004~BenTracker" } // parameters
})

And in Spring MVC the controller: This will be taken care by Poonguzhali
@RequestMapping(value = "/updateGlobalFeatures", method = RequestMethod.PUT)
            public @ResponseBody String updateGlobalFeatures(
                                    @RequestParam("name") String name,
                                    @RequestParam("enabled") boolean enabled,
                                    @RequestParam("resourceId") String resourceId) throws IOException,
                                    JSONException { 

}


